Installing Astra camera driver and running camera using ROS o Install dependencies 
▪ sudo apt install ros-melodic-rgbd-launch ros-melodic-libuvc ros-melodiclibuvc-camera ros-melodic-libuvc-ros o Create ros workspace
 ▪ mkdir -p astra_camera_ws/src ▪ cd astra_camera_ws/ 
▪ catkin_make o Install/Pull the astra camera pkg from github ▪ cd astra_camera/src ▪ git clone https://github.com/orbbec/ros_astra_camera ▪ cd .. 
▪ catkin_make o Add the workspace to bashrc file ▪ echo "source ~/astra_camera/devel/setup.bash" >> ~/.bashrc ▪ source ~/.bashrc o Create astra udev rule ▪ roscd astra_camera ▪ ./scripts/create_udev_rules o Go to astra_camera workspace and compile astra_camera pkg and read data from the camera. ▪ cd astra_camera_ws ▪ catkin_make --pkg astra_camera ▪ source devel/setup.bash o Run camera ▪ roslaunch astra_camera astra.launch ▪ rostopic list o View data using visualization tool ▪ rosrun image_view image_view image:=/camera/rgb/image_raw ▪ rosrun image_view image_view image:=/camera/depth/image_raw ▪ rosrun image_view image_view image:=/camera/ir/image • Installing LIDAR driver and running camera using ROS o Create ros workspace ▪ mkdir -p lidar_ws/src ▪ cd lidar_ws/ ▪ catkin_make o Install/Pull the LIDAR camera pkg from github ▪ cd ~/lidar_ws/src ▪ git clone https://github.com/Slamtec/rplidar_ros